# ASR Error Modeling Project Rules

## Project Overview

This project is a research project on ASR error modeling.
The main goals are:
1. To convert the ASR output on clean speech to the ASR output on noisy speech.
2. To convert the ASR output on noisy speech to the ASR output on clean speech.

## Virtual Environment Usage

When executing commands in the terminal, always activate the environment first:
```bash
source ./.venv/nemo_asr_env/bin/activate
```

## Database Usage

In this project, I use DuckDB as the database.
The DuckDB file is located in the data/sql/ directory.
When you write Python code to connect to the database, you MUST ALWAYS use **read-only mode** to prevent accidental data corruption.
